            . I live opposite to Mr. Baker's house; he <rs id="t18290409-158-viclabel899" type="occupation">sells fowls</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-158-victim1516 t18290409-158-viclabel899"></join>. About half-past seven o'clock in the evening the prisoner was there, with four more <rs id="t18290409-158-deflabel900" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-158-defend1514 t18290409-158-deflabel900"></join>s; I had known him before - he jumped up to the window, took the fowl, and ran away with the others - I pursued the prisoner, and called Stop thief! but he escaped with the fowl - I saw him again the following evening, just by Shoreditch church, and Mr. Baker went after him.</p>
